---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '../config/site';
---

<Layout title={`Domain Setup - ${siteConfig.name}`} description="Domain and subdomain setup instructions">
  <section class="domain-shell">
    <p class="eyebrow">Domain setup</p>
    <h1>Connect your domain after preview approval.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Keep using this preview site for approval and revision requests. For launch, choose the address that fits how
      fast you want to go live and how much DNS control you have.
    </p>

    <div class="domain-grid">
      <article>
        <span>Fastest</span>
        <h2>ProfitsLocal page</h2>
        <p>Use a page on our root domain, such as <strong>profitslocal.com/yourbusiness</strong>.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>No DNS change from you.</li>
          <li>Best for quick launch, proof, or temporary approval.</li>
          <li>You can move to your own domain later.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article>
        <span>Recommended fast launch</span>
        <h2>ProfitsLocal subdomain</h2>
        <p>Use a dedicated address under our domain, such as <strong>yourbusiness.profitslocal.com</strong>.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>No registrar login needed from you.</li>
          <li>Cleaner than a subpage for QR codes, menus, and outreach.</li>
          <li>Usually the easiest option if you want us to handle launch end to end.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article>
        <span>Customer domain</span>
        <h2>Root domain</h2>
        <p>Use your main website address, such as <strong>yourbusiness.com</strong>.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Best when this will replace your official website.</li>
          <li>You or your domain manager add the DNS record we provide.</li>
          <li>After DNS resolves, we verify HTTPS and publish the final link.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article>
        <span>Customer subdomain</span>
        <h2>Subdomain</h2>
        <p>Use a focused address, such as <strong>menu.yourbusiness.com</strong> or <strong>order.yourbusiness.com</strong>.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>This is useful when you already have an official website.</li>
          <li>It is also safer for a menu-only or campaign-specific page.</li>
          <li>The preview utility pages can remain available for revisions.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="handoff-panel">
      <h2>What to send us</h2>
      <p>Tell us which option you prefer. If you want your own domain or subdomain, also send the registrar/DNS provider name and whether you want guided steps or for us to make the DNS change.</p>
      <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.email}`}>{siteConfig.email}</a>
    </div>

    <div class="steps-panel">
      <h2>Own-domain DNS steps</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Approve the dev preview.</li>
        <li>Tell us the exact domain or subdomain you want to use.</li>
        <li>We send the exact DNS target for your project.</li>
        <li>You add a CNAME record at your DNS provider, or invite us to help.</li>
        <li>We verify the Cloudflare Pages custom domain and HTTPS certificate.</li>
        <li>We publish the live link and keep the preview utility page available for revisions.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .domain-shell {
    max-width: 980px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 6rem) 0;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    color: #b9802f;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  h1 {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin-top: 0.8rem;
    color: #17120e;
    font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 7vw, 5.8rem);
    font-weight: 950;
    line-height: 0.92;
  }

  .lede {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    color: #665d55;
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .domain-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  article,
  .handoff-panel,
  .steps-panel {
    border: 1px solid #ddd6cc;
    background: #fffdf8;
    padding: clamp(1rem, 3vw, 1.8rem);
  }

  article span {
    color: #b9802f;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 950;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: 0.6rem;
    color: #17120e;
    font-size: 1.35rem;
  }

  p,
  li {
    color: #665d55;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  ul {
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
  }

  .handoff-panel {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .steps-panel {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  ol {
    margin: 0.75rem 0 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
  }

  .handoff-panel a {
    color: #17120e;
    font-weight: 950;
  }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .domain-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
